{
  "stem": "3928.5",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because I, who always loved, like I told you this, American movies, American theater, you know, and I believed in a American system-- to me, it was like born again.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I never expected to come to the United States, to be honest with you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If the Russians wouldn't have taken over Hungary, I would have stayed in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because I had everything there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I had no reason to come here to seek my fortune.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But when I had-- when they threatened me, to arrest me, I had no other choice to leave, you know, to country.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I was glad.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was very sad when Roosevelt died because I felt like, in the Bible said, you know, like Moses, you know, who-- we always compared with  him, you know, the man who-- who led the people to the Promised Land.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But at the gate, he never went-- stepped through.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's the way I felt about Roosevelt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the same token, I find out this Roosevelt could have done so much more to save a lot more Jews, what he didn't do.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I find out this later on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I find out when he turned the ship back with Jews, you know, because he would not let them immigrate here and wouldn't let them-- give them even a safe haven here.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I find this out later on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he-- afterwards, you know, it's kind of a tarnished of his image in my eye.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But nevertheless, the victory, general, it was great for me because I hated the Nazis, what they stand for, and what they did to the people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I don't think so-- there was ever a happier day in my life than when-- when I heard of V-Day, you know.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
